title: Personal goals of health/fitness club members 2014
summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Percentage of respondents for 13 number of Reasons to Reasons for joinings.
The maximum Percentage of respondents 64.0 is found at Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy and the minimum is found at To gain weight where Reasons to Reasons for joining is 3.0.
The highest Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy has 61.0 more Percentage of respondents than the lowest Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight.

max_summary: This bar chart has 13 columns on the x axis representing Reasons to Reasons for joining, and Percentage of respondents in each Reasons to Reasons for joining on the y axis.
The Percentage of respondents is highest at Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy and lowest at Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight.
Reasons to Reasons for joining To feel better about myself has the second highest value for Percentage of respondents.
There is a difference of 61.0 between the maximum Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy and minimum Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight.
Percentage of respondents at Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy is 64.0 , second place is To feel better about myself at 52.0, and thirdly is To stay in shape at 46.0.
Similar Percentage of respondents is found in Reasons to Reasons for joining To look better, and To lose weight.
The Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy has 1.78 times more Percentage of respondents than average.
Summing up the values of all Reasons to Reasons for joinings, we get total 468.0.
